00:28:44,724 --> 00:28:46,806
So you see them developing series of choices,

681
00:28:46,806 --> 00:28:49,228
plus two or down one, depending on what's going on.

682
00:28:49,228 --> 00:28:51,830
And if the player makes a series of choices

683
00:28:51,830 --> 00:28:53,511
that gets to this point, then.

684
00:28:54,913 --> 00:28:56,394
The marriage score is at an eight.

685
00:28:56,394 --> 00:28:58,135
So Dan and Linda are madly in love.

686
00:28:58,135 --> 00:28:59,375
Their marriage is going great.

687
00:28:59,375 --> 00:29:00,596
They're really reconnecting.

688
00:29:00,596 --> 00:29:03,377
But then you look down here, and Tommy's at a zero.

689
00:29:03,377 --> 00:29:04,818
His dad is being terrible to him.

690
00:29:04,818 --> 00:29:06,699
He has ignored him through literally the entire game.

691
00:29:06,699 --> 00:29:07,639
He's neglecting him.

692
00:29:07,639 --> 00:29:09,020
Tommy is starting to get traumatized.

693
00:29:09,020 --> 00:29:12,701
And then I realized that I had put in these feedback

694
00:29:12,701 --> 00:29:15,783
systems that I showed earlier that said how things are going.

695
00:29:15,783 --> 00:29:17,063
And so the player actually really knows

696
00:29:17,063 --> 00:29:18,264
what these relationships are.

697
00:29:18,264 --> 00:29:21,005
And I started to see these incongruities

698
00:29:21,005 --> 00:29:24,026
when things started to reach the extremes of this dynamic range.

699
00:29:24,026 --> 00:29:24,086
So.

700
00:29:24,867 --> 00:29:28,169
It simply wasn't realistic to have in the same chapter,

701
00:29:28,169 --> 00:29:30,271
Dan saying, oh man, I should make Linda breakfast in bed.

702
00:29:30,271 --> 00:29:33,834
And Linda saying, I hope we didn't wake up Tommy last night.

703
00:29:33,834 --> 00:29:36,155
So obviously, their marriage is going really well.

704
00:29:36,155 --> 00:29:38,377
But then Tommy's sitting in his room with the door closed,

705
00:29:38,377 --> 00:29:40,859
saying, why is my dad such a bully?

706
00:29:40,859 --> 00:29:43,821
It's hard to imagine Linda being madly in love with her husband

707
00:29:43,821 --> 00:29:46,123
at the same time that he's being this awful, awful father.

708
00:29:46,123 --> 00:29:49,045
So once you move to the edges of this range,

709
00:29:49,045 --> 00:29:50,747
these things can start to conflict with each other

710
00:29:50,747 --> 00:29:52,788
in ways that really started to jump out.

711
00:29:52,788 --> 00:29:52,949
So.

712
00:29:53,809 --> 00:29:57,671
Since the player has no control over Tommy or Linda,

713
00:29:57,671 --> 00:29:59,991
then they have to have some level of autonomy in

714
00:29:59,991 --> 00:30:01,872
the way that they deal with these relationships. And

715
00:30:01,872 --> 00:30:04,053
so the solution I came up with was that,

716
00:30:04,053 --> 00:30:06,194
in this case, Linda would actually speak up for

717
00:30:06,194 --> 00:30:08,155
Tommy. And if the roles were reversed, Tommy would

718
00:30:08,155 --> 00:30:09,375
speak up for Linda.

719
00:30:09,375 --> 00:30:11,676
So let's, let's rewind this just a little bit.

